- Rule A: "After event1, event2 must happen." (If event1 occurs at some time t, then at some later time t' > t, event2 must occur.)

- Rule A does not force event1 to occur; it only constrains that if event1 occurs then event2 must follow. That constraint is already satisfied (we have event2), but it does not imply event1 did happen.

Therefore, under the standard interpretation of the scenario, C1 ("Event1 does not happen") is True.

=== Step 2: Solution ===
True

Because event2 has already occurred at the initial moment and Rule B forbids any later events, event1 cannot occur in the timeline (Rule A only constrains consequences if event1 did occur).
